==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stibnite
<hw>Stib"nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
mineral of a lead-gray color and brilliant metallic luster, occurring in
prismatic crystals; sulphide of antimony; -- called also
<altname>antimony glance</altname>, and <altname>gray
antimony</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stibonium</ent>⟦br⟧
